## 3. Real-Time Capabilities: Server-Sent Events (SSE) & Notifications

Unlike traditional web applications that require users to hit "Refresh" to see new data, this CRM portal is truly real-time.

*   **Continuous Connection (SSE):** The backend maintains an open, continuous HTTP connection (`/api/leads/stream`) with the frontend using Server-Sent Events (implemented via `sse.service.js`).
*   **Instant Broadcasts:** Whenever a lead is added (via LinkedIn sync or manual entry), updated, or deleted, the backend instantly broadcasts a JSON payload to all connected clients.
*   **Live UI Updates & Notification Bell:** The Angular dashboard intercepts these events and seamlessly injects the new data into the table. A persistent `notifications` table stores historical alerts, which are displayed as live toasts and an unread counter in the shell navigation.

